\end_inset

.
 The conductivity of a semiconductor can be written generally as
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma=ne\mu_{e}+pe\mu_{h}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
where
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 and
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 are the electron and hole concentrations, respectively,
\begin_inset Formula $q$
\end_inset

 is the fundamental charge, and
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{e}$
\end_inset

 and
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{h}$
\end_inset

 are the electron and hole mobilities, respectively.
 For an intrinsic semiconductor,
\begin_inset Formula $n=p=n_{i}$
\end_inset

 and the conductivity is
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma=n_{i}e(\mu_{e}+\mu_{h})$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
We also know that for intrinsic semiconductors,
\begin_inset Formula $E_{C}-E_{F}=E_{F}-E_{V}=E_{g}/2$
\end_inset

.
 The carrier concentrations are then
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $n=n_{i}=N_{C}e^{-(E_{C}-E_{F})}=N_{C}e^{-E_{g}/2kT}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $p=n_{i}=N_{V}e^{-(E_{F}-E_{V})}=N_{V}e^{-E_{g}/2kT}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
We know from the law of mass action that
\begin_inset Formula $np=n_{i}^{2}$
\end_inset

.
 The intrinsic concentration can then be expressed as
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $n_{i}=\sqrt{N_{C}N_{V}}e^{-(E_{g}/2kT)}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $N_{C}$
\end_inset

 and
\begin_inset Formula $N_{V}$
\end_inset

 are the effective density of states for electrons and holes, given as
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $N_{c}=2(\frac{2\pi m_{e}^{\ast}kT}{h^{2}})^{3/2}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $N_{V}=2(\frac{2\pi m_{h}^{\ast}kT}{h^{2}})^{3/2}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The intrinsic concentration is then
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $n_{i}=2(2\pi kT/h^{2})^{3/2}(m_{e}^{\ast}m_{h}^{\ast})^{3/4}e^{-E_{g}/2kT}$
